                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10793/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Heimke</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Advise Government of Guatemala that Maj. Gen. George W. Davis, former military
                    governor of Porto Rico, former commanding general of the Philippines, and former
                    President of Panama Canal Commission, leaves to-day with his secretary
                    accredited as minister on special mission to represent the United States at
                    opening of railroad.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
